<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06188166 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06188166 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PALO-ALTO; WOMAN; ANIMAL; ASSAULT; RESULT; HOSPITAL; SURGERY  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  When Peggy Gleason opened a door of the Palo Alto office she was working inthis week, she expected a cool breeze.;    Instead, there was a largeRottweiler, which attacked the 77-year-old San Jose woman, leaving seriouswounds on her arm and calf. Gleason has been at Stanford University Hospitalsince the Monday morning attack and had surgery Friday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  77-YEAR-OLD WOMAN NEEDS SKIN GRAFT AFTERDOG ATTACK  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Story also ran on page 2B of the Morning Final edition.  </MEMO><TEXT>     The dog was destroyed at the owner's request, according to a Palo Altoanimal control officer.;    Gleason was going about her office duties at theFife Avenue home where she works once a week. The dog, owned by a friend ofher boss' son, was in the back yard, seemingly secure behind a chain-linkfence. With temperatures near the 90s, Gleason opened the door, hoping to cooloff the room.;    Somehow, the dog was able to get out of the fenced area andinto the house. &quot;He just came right in after me,&quot; she recalled. &quot;I couldn'tbelieve it. Here's this huge animal with these big teeth . . . It was such aterrible experience. You'd never expected the beast to charge at you.&quot;;    Thedog grabbed hold of Gleason's right arm. She was able to free her arm, butthen the dog went for her left calf as she tried to get out of the room.;   In the commotion, some large files crashed between her and the dog, andGleason was able to exit.;    &quot;Fortunately, I was able to get out and yell forhelp,&quot; she said. Two teen-age boys upstairs heard her screams, came down andtook the dog away.;    Doctors performed skin graft surgery on Gleason's armand calf Friday, and she said she might be able to leave the hospital by theend of next week.;    After that, it's back to work, she said. &quot;Now thatthere's no dog there . . . sure I will.&quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  SHELBY GRAD, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Peninsula/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910706  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  325  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday July 6, 199100188166,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>